Ranger Help for: alignment
==========================

SUMMARY:
Rangers are traditionally neutral in alignment, walking the line between
good and evil, order and chaos. This reflects their role as guardians of
the natural balance rather than champions of any particular cause.

While Rangers are not strictly required to maintain a neutral alignment,
straying too far from neutrality will increase the spell point cost of
many skills. Nature does not judge, but it responds best to those who
walk in balance.

A Ranger's declared alignment should ideally remain close to neutral.
Rangers who become too good or too evil may find their connection to
Gaia weakened, making their abilities more costly to use.

